{
  "path": "crates/nyctos-ai/src/adapter/anthropic.rs",
  "line": 230,
  "cap": "SSRF",
  "endpoint": "POST {ai.api_base}/v1/messages (every AI call when ai.runtime = local-llm)",
  "rationale": "AnthropicSdkAdapter constructs the upstream URL with `format!(\"{}/v1/messages\", self.base_url.trim_end_matches('/'))` (anthropic.rs:230). `base_url` flows straight from `cfg.ai.api_base`, which the wizard sets verbatim from SetupRequest.local_llm_url after only `.trim()` (router.rs:312-317, :349-352). No scheme allowlist, no host allowlist, no rejection of loopback / link-local / RFC1918. So `local_llm_url = \"http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/iam/security-credentials/role-name\"` causes every subsequent AI invocation to POST `http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/iam/security-credentials/role-name/v1/messages` from the daemon process — confirming reachability of EC2 IMDS, GCE metadata, or any internal service the daemon can dial. Even when the upstream returns a non-JSON body the SSRF primitive (connect + observe latency / status code) is intact via the AiError::UpstreamRefused string surfaced back through the events bus. Chains with sentinel finding #2 (pre-setup AUTH_BYPASS) for an unauthenticated remote SSRF; stands on its own post-setup as an operator-misconfig / social-engineering vector. Static pass missed it because base_url crosses a configuration boundary (TOML / wizard JSON → adapter struct) the dataflow analyzer treats as a fresh source, not as taint.",
  "suggested_payload_hint": "POST /api/v1/setup body {\"ai_runtime\":\"local-llm\",\"local_llm_url\":\"http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data\",\"sandbox_backend\":\"auto\",\"i_own_this\":true}; trigger any /api/v1/runs that fans out to AI; observe AiEvent::Error carrying the IMDS body fragment."
}

