record_exploration_finding
{
  "path": "crates/nyctos/src/ai_pipeline.rs",
  "line": 193,
  "cap": "AI_BLINDING",
  "endpoint": "POST /api/v1/setup (pre-config window) + every /api/v1/runs",
  "rationale": "All four AI passes gate on `matches!(config.runtime, ConfigAiRuntime::Anthropic)` (ai_pipeline.rs:193 payload synthesis, :505 spec derivation, :796 chain reasoning; exploration follows the same pattern) and silently return a default report otherwise. The wizard accepts `ai_runtime` in {none, anthropic, local-llm, claude-code} (router.rs:240-247) and writes the choice to nyctos.toml without surfacing the no-op consequence; the operator-facing wizard message at router.rs:457 (`Local LLM runtime selected; endpoint will be saved to [ai].api_base`) actively *misleads* — there is no local-llm adapter and `[ai].api_base` has no consumer (see correction above). Chains with finding #2 (pre-setup AUTH_BYPASS): an unauthenticated remote attacker who wins the pre-setup race posts `ai_runtime=\"local-llm\"` (or `\"none\"` / `\"claude-code\"` if the Claude Code binary is absent) and every subsequent scan run executes with **AI passes disabled** while the UI's findings/runs views still render normally — the operator sees an empty AI-side column on each row and (per the documented surface) attributes it to no model output, not a runtime that never started. Net effect: a one-shot config write that durably blinds the defender's AI-augmented scanning, with no log line distinguishing 'AI ran and found nothing' from 'AI never ran'. Distinct from finding #2 (which focused on the sandbox + SSRF angle of the same window) — this is the AI-side leg of the same primitive and is missed by the static pass because it is a *state-machine + silent-no-op* flaw, not a tainted-flow sink. Mitigation: refuse SetupRequest with ai_runtime values that have no compiled adapter; or emit a loud `tracing::warn!` on every pass when the runtime is configured-but-unimplemented; or refuse to start a run with `runtime != none && adapter unavailable`.",
  "suggested_payload_hint": "POST /api/v1/setup body {\"ai_runtime\":\"local-llm\",\"local_llm_url\":\"http://127.0.0.1:1\",\"sandbox_backend\":\"auto\",\"i_own_this\":true}; then POST /api/v1/runs and watch `payload_synthesis: AI runtime is anthropic but no API key configured; skipping` — the same skip path fires for every non-Anthropic runtime, leaving zero AI findings while the run completes 'green'."
}

