record_exploration_finding
{
  "path": "crates/nyctos-core/src/repo/git.rs",
  "line": 211,
  "cap": "OS_COMMAND",
  "endpoint": "POST /api/v1/projects/:project_id/repos (auth_ref=\"ssh-key:<path>\") then any /api/v1/runs that triggers ingest_git",
  "rationale": "apply_env composes GIT_SSH_COMMAND with `format!(\"ssh -i {} -o IdentitiesOnly=yes -o StrictHostKeyChecking=accept-new\", p.display())` (git.rs:209-216). `p` is the PathBuf carried by `GitAuth::SshKey`. `GitAuth::parse` accepts the post-colon segment verbatim — `\"ssh-key\" => Ok(GitAuth::SshKey(PathBuf::from(value)))` (repo/mod.rs:92) — with no whitespace, no shell-metachar, and no leading-dash rejection. git invokes GIT_SSH_COMMAND via `/bin/sh -c <cmd> <host> <git-command>` (documented; child_process use_shell=1 path), so an operator-supplied auth_ref of the shape `ssh-key:/tmp/k$(touch /tmp/pwn)` or `ssh-key:; touch /tmp/pwn ;#` lands in the shell-expanded ssh invocation and executes under the daemon UID. session-0014's new `validate_git_auth_ref` (router.rs:864-885) gates only on `GitAuth::parse` succeeding — which it always does for `ssh-key:<anything>` — so the freshly added validator does NOT close this hole. Distinct from finding #10 (`ext::` URL-side injection via `source_url_or_path`): different operator field (`auth_ref`), different sink (env-var GIT_SSH_COMMAND, not argv), and the new validator was *specifically* introduced to lock down auth_ref while leaving this primitive intact. Static pass missed it because PathBuf::from + format!() looks like an inert string-format with no exec sink — the dangerous behavior is git's documented shell-invocation of the env, two crates downstream.",
  "suggested_payload_hint": "POST /api/v1/projects/proj-x/repos {\"name\":\"r1\",\"source_kind\":\"git\",\"source_url_or_path\":\"git@github.com:any/repo.git\",\"auth_ref\":\"ssh-key:/tmp/k; touch /tmp/nyctos-pwn ;#\",\"i_own_this\":true}; trigger ingest via POST /api/v1/runs targeting that repo; observe /tmp/nyctos-pwn appear under the daemon UID. Mitigate by shell-quoting `p.display()` after rejecting any path containing `'`, or by switching to argv-style `git -c core.sshCommand=...` with proper argv quoting, or by refusing any PathBuf whose components contain shell metacharacters at parse time."
}

