{
  "path": "crates/nyctos-core/src/state.rs",
  "line": 11,
  "cap": "INSECURE_FILE_PERMISSIONS",
  "endpoint": "<state>/traces directory tree",
  "rationale": "`SUBDIRS` adds `\"traces\"` (state.rs:11-12) and `StateDir::ensure` creates it via the same generic `create_dir_all` loop the other subdirs use — inheriting the default 0755 mode (umask-dependent). The `secrets` subdir gets explicit 0700 hardening elsewhere in `StateDir::ensure` because it holds credentials; `traces` now holds the AI exploration audit JSONL files, which encode every endpoint the agent probed, every finding rationale (including suggested payload hints — full attack recipes), and the full sequence of `record_exploration_finding` summaries. That body is at least as sensitive as a scanner finding row (the operator-side `findings` table is sqlite-only, not world-readable), and arguably more so because it includes payload hints that haven't been promoted through Quarantine yet (the verifier may discard them later, but the audit log keeps them). With default 0755 on `<state>/traces/<run_id>/` and 0644 on each `<task_id>.jsonl`, any local user on the host can `find <state>/traces -name '*.jsonl' -exec cat {} +` and harvest the entire exploration history — including the payload hints needed to mount the same attacks the agent surfaced. Compounds findings #21 and #22 above: even when the path-traversal and symlink-follow vectors are blocked, the *intended* artefact path is still world-readable. Static pass missed it because there's no mode literal to grep on — it's the *absence* of a `set_permissions(0o700)` call after `create_dir_all`, mirroring the secrets-subdir treatment. Fix: extend `StateDir::ensure` to apply `std::os::unix::fs::PermissionsExt::set_mode(0o700)` on the `traces` subdir at creation; in `write_exploration_audit_jsonl`, set `OpenOptions::mode(0o600)` (Unix ext) before opening. Document the threat model: 'audit JSONL is operator-confidential; assume single-tenant host or harden filesystem ACLs'.",
  "suggested_payload_hint": "As a non-daemon local UID after a scan completes: `ls -la <state>/traces/` (expect mode 0755), `cat <state>/traces/<any-run-id>/<any-task-id>.jsonl` succeeds and dumps full audit log incl. payload hints. Verifier-side: assert that after `StateDir::ensure`, `std::fs::metadata(state.traces())?.permissions().mode() & 0o777 == 0o700` — currently false. Same assertion for any JSONL file post-write."
}

