session-appended 2026-05-21 expl-demo follow-up #14 (HEAD cba7f0e session-0032 + uncommitted run_findings diff). Session-0032 committed only docs/ai-runtime.md prose (per-call cap allocation ladder, AgentLoop sub-bucket rationale) + sentinel re-anchor. The substantive new attack surface is the UNCOMMITTED diff that adds the v4 `run_findings` join table (migrations/0004_run_findings.sql), promotes `CURRENT_SCHEMA_VERSION` to 4 (schema.rs:14), dual-writes from `FindingStore::upsert` (finding.rs:188-251), introduces `FindingStore::list_run_membership` (finding.rs:259-270), and rewrites the run-scoped findings classifier in `findings_for_run` (router.rs:1302-1391) to emit `New` / `Regressed` / `Closed` / `Unchanged` via current-vs-prior membership comparison plus a synthetic Closed-row injection path. All 28 prior findings re-anchor unchanged.

Four net-new findings on the run_findings classifier path emitted below: #29 CROSS_RUN_REPO_LEAK (Closed-row fetch bypasses run/repo scope), #30 N_PLUS_1_DOS (sequential per-id finding fetch for every absent prior member), #31 CLASSIFIER_LATEST_STATUS_MISCOMPARE (diff_status compares prior-run snapshot against LATEST collapsed `findings.status`, not the current run's run_findings.status), #32 CURRENT_ROW_USES_COLLAPSED_RUN_ID (current-row set selected via `list_filtered` on collapsed `findings.run_id`, so a finding re-observed under a later run vanishes from the older run's view even though the new join table records membership for both). Total: 32 findings.

