session-appended 2026-05-21 expl-demo follow-up (HEAD 53e1b52 + uncommitted ShimStatus→ShimReport diff in nyctos-sandbox/{src/backend/process.rs,src/bin/nyx_sandbox_shim.rs,src/lib.rs,src/shim.rs,tests/escape.rs}).
TARGETS: (none) — survey-only of uncommitted nyctos-sandbox diff
ALLOWED HOSTS: (none)
Committed delta vs session-0035 anchor (c705ce4): no changes to nyctos-sandbox beyond what session-0033/0034 landed; the four findings #36-#39 anchor against the committed `ShimStatus` shape.
Uncommitted delta widens the wire format from `ShimStatus` (single enum) to `ShimReport { status, refusals: Vec<String> }` and surfaces refusals on `SandboxOutcome.refusals` (lib.rs:342-348). Three new findings appended below:
  #40 RESOURCE_EXHAUSTION   process.rs:152  read_to_end on status pipe has no size cap; combines with #36's forge primitive for unbounded daemon-RAM growth
  #41 LOG_INJECTION         shim.rs:60      ShimReport.refusals is an unconstrained Vec<String> the parent forwards verbatim to SandboxOutcome.refusals; chain with #36 lets a sandboxee inject ANSI/control sequences (CLI) or HTML (UI) into operator-visible refusal text
  #42 FD_LEAK_TOCTOU        birdcage.rs:282 open_status_pipe uses libc::pipe + separate fcntl(read_fd, F_SETFD, FD_CLOEXEC); write end NEVER gets FD_CLOEXEC at all; concurrent tokio fork-exec on another thread inherits one or both pipe ends → parent's read_to_end never EOFs → drive_to_completion blocks forever (DoS on the daemon worker)
All 39 prior findings re-confirmed against the uncommitted diff: #36/#37/#38/#39 anchors shift from `read_status_fd`/`write_status_frame_to_fd3` to `read_report_fd`/`write_report_to_fd3` but the underlying primitives and line numbers within those functions are unchanged. Total: 42 findings.

