session-appended 2026-05-21 expl-demo follow-up #21 (HEAD 2c95405 session-0038 + uncommitted nyctos-sandbox snapshot_from feature). Diff vs session-0037 = first appearance of `SandboxOpts.snapshot_from: Option<PathBuf>` (lib.rs:289-299) + builder `with_snapshot_from` (:325) + `apply_snapshot_from` helper (backend/mod.rs:24-46) wired into every backend (process.rs:78, birdcage.rs:69, firecracker.rs:145, libkrun.rs:127) with the resulting `TempDir` stashed on `RunningChild.scratch_snapshot` (process.rs:48-56) for RAII cleanup. The feature provides workspace write-isolation but the snapshot path delegates the actual copy to `crate::workspace::snapshot` (workspace.rs:33) which preserves in-tree symlinks (copy_tree at :70-99, reflink_tree at :136-163, clonefile fast path at :112-133). No production caller yet — `with_snapshot_from` is exercised only by the three new unit tests in mod.rs and process.rs. The feature lands one session before any verifier/chain-runner wiring; the holes below are best fixed now while no consumer has cemented assumptions.

Two new findings appended below: (#42) symlink escape — in-tree symlinks pointing outside `snapshot_from` are reproduced verbatim under the snapshot, and `ProcessSandbox` (which has zero filesystem isolation by design — see sentinel finding #2 chain notes) resolves them at syscall time inside the sandboxed child, defeating the workspace write-isolation invariant the feature was added to provide; (#43) DoS via unbounded `copy_tree` fallback — `snapshot_from` whose tree contains hard-link / loopback / very-large content exhausts disk + worker-thread time on every non-COW filesystem (tmpfs, ext4 without reflink, every macOS volume that is not the APFS data volume). Total: 31 findings.

