session-appended 2026-05-21 expl-demo follow-up #22 (HEAD 2c95405 +
  uncommitted nyctos-sandbox snapshot_from diff, same diff the #21 block
  scouted). #21 already booked the symlink-escape (in-tree symlinks
  reproduced verbatim → ProcessSandbox follows them) and the
  copy_tree-fallback DoS. Three additional findings appended below that
  exercise the SAME diff from different angles #21 did not cover:
  (#44) workspace-override leaks every OTHER `SandboxOpts` field that
  references workspace-relative paths — `cwd`, `allow_read`,
  `allow_write` — back to the source tree; the docstring at
  lib.rs:325-326 explicitly promises composition with other setters,
  which the implementation does not deliver. (#45) top-level `src`
  symlink is dereferenced by the macOS `clonefile(src, dst, 0)` fast
  path because flags=0 omits `CLONE_NOFOLLOW` (distinct from #42 which
  scouted NESTED symlinks under a non-symlink src). (#46) `RunningChild`
  field declaration order (child → status_fd → scratch_snapshot) plus
  `kill_on_drop`'s fire-and-forget SIGKILL race the `TempDir`'s
  recursive `remove_dir_all` against a Firecracker/Libkrun VMM that may
  still hold virtio-fs / disk-image mappings on the snapshot tree.
  Total: 46 findings.

