session-appended 2026-05-21 expl-demo follow-up (HEAD 5059ade session-0040). New attack surface: per-step COW snapshot isolation for non-terminal chain steps (chain_runner.rs:380-387). Terminal step deliberately runs against the parent workspace so its `chain.sentinel` write survives `Sandbox::wait` and is observable to `eval_terminal_probe`. `execute_pass` (chain_runner.rs:303-309) is called twice when `replay_stable_check` is set, with `clear_sentinel` resetting only the sentinel file between passes. One new finding emitted; the snapshot-symlink hazards from sentinel #21/#22 (workspace.rs copy_tree honouring in-tree symlinks) carry over unchanged to this consumer because session-0040 wires `with_snapshot_from(run.workspace.clone())` directly without a between-pass canonicalisation step.

