{
  "path": "crates/nyctos-ai/src/adapter/claude_code.rs",
  "line": 238,
  "cap": "CRED_EXPOSURE",
  "endpoint": "ClaudeCodeAdapter::agent_loop -> Command::new spawn of `claude` CLI",
  "rationale": "`Command::new(&self.binary.path).arg(\"--print\")...spawn()` at claude_code.rs:238-258 inherits the full parent process environment with no `.env_clear()` or per-var `.env_remove()` calls and no allowlist. The nyctos daemon's env legitimately holds high-value secrets needed for OTHER adapters and integrations: `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` (nyctos-ai/src/adapter/anthropic.rs reads it from env), `GITHUB_TOKEN` / `GH_TOKEN` (nyctos/src/cmd/pr_comment.rs gh-api auth), `NYCTOS_WEBHOOK_SECRET` (api/src/webhook.rs HMAC), database URLs (`NYCTOS_DB_URL`), and operator-set passthrough vars. The spawned `claude` binary executes inside the SAME process env, which means: (i) a `claude` binary tampered with via PATH shadowing or supply-chain compromise reads all of these via `std::env::vars()`; (ii) `claude`'s own subprocess tree (any tool-use shell-out) inherits them recursively (Rust's Command default inherits); (iii) the env appears in `/proc/<pid>/environ` of the child where any colocated unprivileged process can scrape it. The adapter's only sandbox boundary is `binary.path` being an absolute path resolved at startup (claude_code.rs:~80 binary discovery), which prevents PATH-shadowing of the spawn target itself but does NOT contain what the child does with the env it receives. The `--strict-mcp-config` / `--allowed-tools` style flags are passed (lines 239-244) but env scoping is orthogonal to MCP scoping. Static pass missed because env inheritance is implicit (the absence of `.env_clear()`); a static check would need to enumerate Command builders and flag default-inherit as a vuln, which is rarely encoded as a rule. Distinct from sentinel #4 / #16 (CRED_EXPOSURE on router.rs / git.rs) — those leak secrets via response bodies or git URL flags; this leaks via OS-level env to a long-running child process tree.",
  "suggested_payload_hint": "Reproduce in a test rig: set `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-redacted-canary-12345` in the daemon env, replace `claude` with a fixture binary that on startup writes `std::env::vars().collect()` to a file in cwd, drive ClaudeCodeAdapter::run_task once. Observe canary in the dump. Same for `GITHUB_TOKEN`. Mitigation: build the Command with explicit `.env_clear()` then re-add only the minimal allowlist actually needed by `claude` (HOME, PATH for tool discovery, TERM, LANG, and any `CLAUDE_*` config vars). Add a regression test that asserts `Command` for the claude spawn does not contain `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` / `GITHUB_TOKEN` / `NYCTOS_*` keys when constructed with a tampered parent env. Bonus: if `claude` itself needs API credentials, pass them via a one-shot stdin handshake or a per-call config file in the scratch tempdir (claude_code.rs:228) rather than env, so they are not visible in /proc/PID/environ for the child's lifetime."
}

