  "rationale": "copy_recursive at local.rs:218-243 reproduces source symlinks verbatim in the destination snapshot via `let target = std::fs::read_link(&src_child)?; std::os::unix::fs::symlink(&target, &dst_child)?;` (lines 228-230). `target` is whatever bytes the source symlink points at — arbitrary absolute paths (`/etc/passwd`, `/root/.aws/credentials`, `/proc/self/environ`) or relative-escaping (`../../../host/secret`) are written into the snapshot tree unchanged. A repo cloned via `nyctos repos add` that contains `secret -> /etc/shadow` lands in the snapshot as the same dangling symlink. Subsequent stages that walk the snapshot with symlink-following semantics — the embedded nyx engine's static scanners (ai_pipeline.rs:417 path-traversal sentinel was for a different leg), the sandbox workspace cloner (nyctos-sandbox/src/workspace.rs already has its own SANDBOX_ESCAPE finding at #41/42 but for a different code path), and any AI exploration worker that uses `tokio::fs::read_to_string` — dereference the symlink and read host data into the scanner's context window or finding payloads, where it is then logged / shipped to AI provider / persisted in `findings` table. This is the **non-sandbox** ingest path (`crates/nyctos-core/src/repo/local.rs`, used by repo ingestion before the sandbox workspace ever materialises) — distinct from sentinel #41 (workspace.rs:72 in nyctos-sandbox) which is the sandbox-side workspace builder. Both paths reproduce the same class of bug but in different crates and at different lifecycle stages; mitigations applied to nyctos-sandbox/src/workspace.rs do not patch the core/repo ingest. The `chmod_minus_w_recursive` defender below (line 246) explicitly SKIPS symlinks (line 250-252) so it offers no defence-in-depth. Static pass missed because the cross-crate duplication makes single-file taint tracking insufficient — the same bug class shows up in two crates with different surrounding code and only one was flagged.",
  "suggested_payload_hint": "Stage a fixture repo under tests/fixtures/repos/with_escape_symlink/ containing `escape -> /etc/passwd` and `escape_rel -> ../../../../etc/hosts`. Invoke `LocalRepo::snapshot(&fixture_path, &snapshot_dst)` and assert (a) `snapshot_dst.join(\"escape\")` exists as a symlink, (b) `std::fs::read_to_string(snapshot_dst.join(\"escape\"))` returns the host /etc/passwd contents (proving the snapshot did not absorb-by-value or reject). Then drive the downstream pipeline that walks the snapshot (the static nyx scanner suffices) and grep its findings/log output for tell-tale strings (`root:x:0:0` for /etc/passwd, `localhost` for /etc/hosts) to confirm escape into the scanner's reach. Mitigation options, pick one: (i) reject snapshot when copy_recursive encounters any symlink whose `read_link` target is absolute OR contains `..` segments OR resolves outside `src` after canonicalize; (ii) absorb-by-value (copy the dereferenced regular file contents, dropping the symlink-ness); (iii) replace the link with an empty placeholder file plus a sidecar JSON noting the dropped link target for forensics. Add property test: random symlink targets x { absolute, relative-escape, in-tree } — assert no resulting snapshot entry's canonicalized path escapes `dst`."
}

