session-appended 2026-05-21 expl-demo follow-up #7 (HEAD eac2cd2
  session-0004 deferred + uncommitted ChainRecord/RepoRecord hoist
  on top of it). The session-0004 commit MOVED `Repo`, `RepoSource`,
  `GitAuth` from `nyctos-core::repo` into `nyctos-types::repo` and
  added `Serialize + Deserialize + TS` derives; the uncommitted
  follow-up moves `RepoRecord` and `ChainRecord` the same way (xtask
  registers them all in `render()` so types.gen.ts now ships
  `GitAuth`, `RepoSource`, `Repo`, `RepoRecord`, `ChainRecord`).
  Previously these were Rust-internal types reachable only from the
  operator-edited TOML (`nyctos_core::config::load`); the type
  system enforced "no wire-deserialised Repo descriptors". The
  refactor removes that enforcement WITHOUT adding a per-field
  validator on the new Deserialize impls. The router today still
  consumes per-call DTOs (router.rs:710 `CreateRepoRequest`,
  router.rs:789 `PatchRepoRequest`) keyed by raw strings, so the
  sinks (git.rs:87-103 std::env::var + bearer-injection;
  git.rs:209-216 GIT_SSH_COMMAND with attacker path; local.rs:119
  arbitrary LocalPath snapshot read) are NOT reachable from HTTP
  today. The moment a single future axum handler is added that
  takes `Json<Repo>` / `Json<RepoSource>` / `Json<GitAuth>` (or
  inserts one of these types into a DB row that later round-trips
  via a different deserialise boundary, e.g. a project-config-import
  endpoint that consumes the same TOML shape via JSON), three
  latent vulnerabilities materialise simultaneously — none of which
  the static pass will fire on because the deserialiser is correct,
  the sink is correct, and the only "missing" piece is a validator
  in between that the original threat model placed at the operator
  -edited-TOML layer. Three new findings appended below: #78
  LOCALPATH_DESERIALIZE_PATH_TRAVERSAL, #79
  TOKEN_ENV_DESERIALIZE_EXFIL, #80 SSHKEY_DESERIALIZE_KEY_PIVOT.
  Pre-existing findings #1-#77 still apply unchanged. Total: 80
  findings.

