record_exploration_finding
{
  "path": "crates/nyctos-types/src/repo.rs",
  "line": 27,
  "cap": "LOCALPATH_DESERIALIZE_PATH_TRAVERSAL",
  "endpoint": "internal: `RepoSource` (nyctos-types/src/repo.rs:27-34) derives `Deserialize` and exposes the `LocalPath { path: PathBuf }` variant with NO `#[serde(deserialize_with)]` validator, NO allow-listed root, NO refusal of absolute paths, and NO refusal of `..` segments. The sink is `nyctos_core::repo::local::SnapshotBackend::from_dir(path)` (crates/nyctos-core/src/repo/local.rs:119 — caller at repo/mod.rs:257 takes the deserialised PathBuf and hands it directly to the read-only snapshot backend, which traverses the path with `std::fs::read_dir` / `ignore::WalkBuilder` and indexes every file it finds into the per-run workspace under `<state>/repos/<name>/checkout/`). Snapshot output is then exposed to the scan pipeline and (via candidate evidence + finding-detail UI) eventually to the SPA at `frontend/src/pages/Findings/FindingDetail.tsx`.",
  "rationale": "Pre-session-0004 the type system enforced \"`RepoSource::LocalPath` only constructed from `RepoSourceConfig::LocalPath { path }`\" — `RepoSourceConfig` lives in `nyctos_core::config` and is reached only via `load_config(path: &Path)` reading the operator-edited TOML on disk. The trust boundary was the FILESYSTEM ITSELF: anyone able to write to `nyctos.toml` was already root-equivalent on the host. Session-0004's hoist (commits eac2cd2 + the uncommitted ts-rs work) moved `Repo` and `RepoSource` into `nyctos-types` and added `#[derive(Deserialize, TS)]`. Two new exposures result:\n\n(1) **Wire-reachable arbitrary-file read primitive** — the moment any axum (or other serde) handler accepts a `Json<Repo>` or `Json<RepoSource>` or `Json<{ source: RepoSource }>` payload (e.g. a future `POST /api/v1/projects/:id/repos:import-config` endpoint that takes the same shape as the TOML config — a natural extension given the docs at `docs/PROJECT_ENTITY_PLAN.md`), an authenticated SPA caller submits `{\"LocalPath\": {\"path\": \"/etc/passwd\"}}` (or `/proc/self/environ`, or `/root/.ssh/id_ed25519`, or `~/.aws/credentials`). `repo_from_config` (repo/mod.rs:67-82) produces a `Repo { source: RepoSource::LocalPath { path } }`; `ingest` (repo/mod.rs:248-265) dispatches to `local::ingest` which calls `SnapshotBackend::from_dir(path)`; the WalkBuilder reads `path` recursively, ingests file content into the per-run workspace, and persists it. The candidate-finding evidence rows surface excerpts of every file under that path to the SPA. The static pass cannot fire because (i) the deserialiser is correct (PathBuf accepts any string), (ii) the sink is correct (read-only directory snapshot is the documented behaviour), (iii) the route does not exist yet so no flow analysis has a sink to anchor on.\n\n(2) **Test-bench accidental exposure** — the integration test surface for the new types-crate is small but the test-only Deserialize is identical to the production one. If a future test author writes `serde_json::from_str::<Repo>(&user_supplied_fixture_string)` (e.g. property-based testing via `proptest`-style serialised fixtures, or replay of audit-log entries that contain Repo descriptors), the same primitive lands inside the test binary. Sandbox lane tests run with the daemon's uid; the absolute-path read leaks lane state into test output.\n\nTwo concrete attack chains:\n\n(A) **Bearer-credential exfil via /proc/self/environ**: a SPA-authenticated low-privilege session that lands a future `Json<Repo>` endpoint submits `{name: \"x\", source: {LocalPath: {path: \"/proc/self/environ\"}}, i_own_this: true, project_id: \"any\"}`. The local snapshot reads the null-separated `KEY=VALUE` block of the DAEMON's own process — which today includes the GitHub bearer the daemon is currently using for an in-flight repo clone (apply_bearer_token_env at git.rs:245-251 sets `GIT_CONFIG_VALUE_1=Authorization: Bearer <token>` in the child env, but the snapshot read is against the parent daemon's environ, which holds operator-configured env-vars including any `GH_TOKEN` / `GITHUB_TOKEN` named by `GitAuth::TokenEnv` and read via `std::env::var` at git.rs:88-89; on Linux the parent's environ is `0400` mode by uid but the daemon reads its own environ with no privilege barrier). The file content becomes the snapshot; the finding UI surfaces snippets; the SPA caller harvests the bearer.\n\n(B) **SSH key exfil via /home/<daemon>/.ssh/**: same shape, `path: \"/home/eli/.ssh\"` → snapshot reads private keys + known_hosts. The daemon process must have read access (which it does for its own home).\n\nCompounds with #79 and #80 below — all three findings share the same architectural defect (Deserialize hoist without validator) at three different sinks.\n\nDistinct from prior sentinel findings: this is NOT #65-class (PATH_TRAVERSAL on payload-shape coverage in the candidate-emission layer), NOT #11-class (PATH_TRAVERSAL via unchecked Path::join in the audit-log writer), NOT #14 / #24 (PATH_TRAVERSAL in StateDir helpers). It is a NEW class: latent-arbitrary-file-read primitive opened by widening the Deserialize-reachable surface of a type whose original threat model assumed only operator-on-disk-TOML construction.\n\nStatic pass missed because (i) at the `nyctos-types::repo` site the type carries no taint annotation and no sink — it's a pure data shape; (ii) at the `nyctos-core::repo::local::ingest` site the sink is correct under the original threat model and the static pass sees no untrusted source flowing into the PathBuf; (iii) NO connecting route exists today, so a whole-program reachability analyser sees no path from network input to the sink. The bug is the ABSENCE of a per-field validator that would constrain the type's Deserialize impl regardless of where it gets called from.\n\nMitigations (recommend 1+3 minimum; 4 is the long-term architectural fix):\n\n(1) **Add `#[serde(deserialize_with)]` to the `path: PathBuf` field** of `RepoSource::LocalPath` that enforces (a) the path is absolute, (b) the path is canonicalised, (c) the canonical path begins with one of an allow-listed set of roots from a runtime-injected `LocalPathPolicy` (or, more conservatively, fails closed if no policy is set in the deserialiser's thread-local context). serde supports thread-local policy via `with` and a custom newtype `LocalSnapshotPath(PathBuf)` carrying the validated invariant; replace `path: PathBuf` with `path: LocalSnapshotPath` in `RepoSource::LocalPath`.\n\n(2) **Split the Deserialize surface from the in-memory descriptor**: introduce `RepoSourceWire { Git { ... }, LocalPath { path: String } }` as the Deserialize-only shape, and require an explicit `RepoSourceWire::into_repo_source(&LocalPathPolicy)` conversion that validates the path against the policy. The hoisted `nyctos-types::RepoSource` then has NO Deserialize derive (re-add `#[derive(Serialize, TS)]` only); inbound construction is impossible without the policy-aware conversion. The static pass can then fire on `serde_json::from_str::<RepoSource>(...)` calls because the trait bound is absent.\n\n(3) **Document the threat model explicitly in the type doc-comment** at nyctos-types/src/repo.rs:21: \"NOTE: `LocalPath::path` derives Deserialize but assumes the deserialise-source is an operator-edited config file. Routing this type through `serde_json::from_str` from a network handler is a CVE waiting to happen — use `RepoSourceWire` (TODO) instead.\" Today the doc comment says nothing about the trust boundary; a future maintainer adding the `import-config` endpoint has no signal.\n\n(4) **Add a deny-deserialise lint** — a build.rs-time check that scans the workspace for `Json<Repo>`, `Json<RepoSource>`, `from_str::<Repo>`, etc. and fails the build unless the call site carries an explicit `#[allow(nyctos_lint::deserialise_from_network)]` annotation. Heavy but durable.\n\n(5) **Behavioural regression test**: `repo_source_localpath_refuses_proc_self_environ` — under mitigation (1), assert `serde_json::from_str::<RepoSource>(r#\"{\"LocalPath\":{\"path\":\"/proc/self/environ\"}}\"#)` returns `Err`. Today asserts `Ok`.",
  "suggested_payload_hint": "Verifier seed (unit test in nyctos-types/tests/ or nyctos-core/src/repo/mod.rs's tests module): `repo_source_deserialise_arbitrary_absolute_path_succeeds_today` — `let json = r#\"{\"LocalPath\":{\"path\":\"/etc/passwd\"}}\"#; let parsed: nyctos_types::repo::RepoSource = serde_json::from_str(json).expect(\"deserialise\"); match parsed { RepoSource::LocalPath { path } => assert_eq!(path, std::path::PathBuf::from(\"/etc/passwd\")), _ => panic!() }`. Today: passes — demonstrates the absent-validator gap. Under mitigation (1): assert `serde_json::from_str::<RepoSource>(json).is_err()` and the error references a `LocalSnapshotPath` policy violation. End-to-end: add a temporary axum route `POST /test/import-repo-source` that takes `Json<RepoSource>` and feeds it to `ingest`; submit the `/etc/passwd` JSON; today observe the file content in the per-run workspace; under mitigation (2) observe a 400 BadRequest before any IO. Compound reproducer: combine with #79's TokenEnv JSON and #80's SshKey JSON in one Repo payload and assert all three are refused under combined mitigations."
}

