  "rationale": "The `target_base_url` field on CreateProjectRequest (router.rs:532) and PatchProjectRequest (router.rs:587) is a raw `Option<String>` that goes straight from JSON body through `req.target_base_url.as_deref()` (:562) into the store with NO scheme/host validation: no URL parse, no allowlist of `http`/`https`, no rejection of `file://`, `gopher://`, `ssh://`, `git+ssh://`, or the AWS/GCP metadata IPs (`169.254.169.254`, `metadata.google.internal`, `100.100.100.200` for Aliyun). The value is then surfaced verbatim into the merged compose YAML as the `x-nyx-target-base-url` extension key (crates/nyctos-sandbox/src/env/compose.rs:231-234), and the env-builder passes the same string into ProjectOverrides for `merge` (crates/nyctos-sandbox/src/env/mod.rs:237-240). Any downstream tool / service spec that reads the extension key as a probe target (Postman/Newman containers, custom curl-based smoke tests in the user-supplied compose stack, the upcoming `nyctos-sandbox` HTTP probe) will hit an attacker-chosen origin from inside the lane that holds the operator's `test.env` secrets bundle. This is the classic 'configurable base URL that becomes an SSRF gadget' surface and is exactly the kind of finding the static pass cannot reach because it requires correlating the API DTO with the downstream sandbox consumer two crates away.",
  "suggested_payload_hint": "POST /api/v1/projects {name:\"ssrf\", target_base_url:\"http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/iam/security-credentials/\"} then trigger any scan/test path that resolves the URL; alt: `gopher://internal-redis:6379/_SET%20foo%20bar`; alt: `file:///etc/passwd` (resolves through curl-based service tests inside the compose lane)."
}

