  "line": 56,
  "cap": "TYPE_DRIFT_VS_VALIDATION",
  "endpoint": "TS contract bridge: ProjectRecord (types.gen.ts) vs PatchProjectRequest (router.rs)",
  "rationale": "The diff promotes `ProjectRecord` into the ts_rs-derived public bridge (nyctos-types/src/project.rs:56-65; xtask/src/main.rs:122 now `decl_of::<ProjectRecord>()`), so the SPA imports it as the canonical projects shape from `types.gen.ts:174`. The generated TS shape declares `env_config_json: string | null` — i.e. an opaque serialised blob — but the server-side request DTO `PatchProjectRequest::env_config` (crates/nyctos-api/src/router.rs:589-591) is `serde_json::Value`, i.e. structured. There is now NO single typed contract describing how a TS caller should mutate env_config: the GET returns a string, the PATCH expects an object on a *differently-named* field (`env_config` vs `env_config_json`), and the same operator-facing dialog in ProjectAddModal.tsx / ProjectDetail.tsx must do a manual JSON.parse/JSON.stringify across the boundary. Two concrete hazards land in the next refactor that 'follows the types': (a) a SPA that round-trips the fetched `ProjectRecord` as a PATCH body will silently double-serialise env_config (the server stores the JSON-encoded *string* of the previous JSON-encoded string, losing structure on the next read); (b) a SPA that posts the raw object to `env_config_json` (matching the GET field name) gets BadRequest from serde, but a future server tweak that adds `#[serde(alias=\"env_config_json\")]` for symmetry would resurrect the env-injection path of finding #89 with no warning. The bridge change is what surfaces this asymmetry into a load-bearing public API. Static analysis cannot see it because the inconsistency lives in the *intersection* of two crates plus a code-generator.",
  "suggested_payload_hint": "Reproduce: `curl -X PATCH /api/v1/projects/:id -d '{\"env_config_json\":\"{\\\"LD_PRELOAD\\\":\\\"/tmp/x.so\\\"}\"}'` then GET the same id and observe the field is a JSON-encoded JSON string; or send the same body twice via the SPA flow and watch the value gain an additional layer of `\\\"` quoting each round."
}

