{"path":"crates/nyctos-types/src/project.rs","line":99,"cap":"TS_CONTRACT_DRIFT_DATA_LOSS","rationale":"PatchProjectRequest::env_config carries #[ts(type = \"unknown\")] but no #[ts(optional)]. The generated TS at frontend/src/api/types.gen.ts:185 emits `env_config: unknown` (mandatory) while description/target_base_url retain `?` (optional). TS callers MUST send env_config on every PATCH; the only valid value that means \"don't touch it\" semantically is `null`. But the Rust deserialize_tri_state_json maps both missing-key AND explicit-null to TriStateJson::Null, which the router merges as CLEAR. Outcome: every well-typed FE PATCH that updates only description/target_base_url silently wipes env_config_json (every project env secret) on first run. The Rust side IS tri-state correct (omit → Unset → no change), but the TS contract forbids omitting, so the safe path is unreachable from the typed FE. Static pass missed: each crate is internally consistent; the bug is the cross-language contract.","endpoint":"PATCH /api/v1/projects/:project_id","suggested_payload_hint":"FE: api.patchProject(id,{description:'x'}) compiles ONLY after adding env_config:null; on send, env_config_json column is set to NULL. Fix: add #[ts(optional)] alongside #[ts(type=\"unknown\")] so TS emits env_config?:unknown."}
{"path":"crates/nyctos-types/src/repo.rs","line":104,"cap":"TYPE_NARROWING_LOSS","rationale":"CreateRepoRequest::source_kind is `String` in Rust with the doc comment claiming the router validates against the closed `git|local-path|github|gitlab|local` set at handler time. The new generated TS (types.gen.ts:162) declares `source_kind: string` — but the pre-hoist FE client.ts:179 declared `source_kind: RepoSourceKind` (the 5-value union still exported at client.ts:178). Hoisting the DTO into nyctos-types DROPPED the FE-side union narrowing: TS compiler no longer rejects `source_kind: 'sftp'` or arbitrary typos. PatchRepoRequest::source_kind has the same regression. Recovery path requires either a custom TS alias re-export that intersects with RepoSourceKind, or a #[ts(type = \"RepoSourceKind\")] override on the Rust field plus a re-export of the alias from types.gen.ts. Compounds with the OS_COMMAND finding on git_ls_remote_probe (router.rs:976): the wider TS type lets a misuse send `source_kind: 'git'` with any string, but also surfaces previously-unreachable handler branches if any future code dispatches on the raw string.","endpoint":"POST /api/v1/projects/:project_id/repos and PATCH .../repos/:name","suggested_payload_hint":"FE test: `const r: CreateRepoRequest = { name:'x', source_kind:'arbitrary-typo', source_url_or_path:'./', i_own_this:true }` — today compiles cleanly; pre-hoist failed type-check at source_kind."}
{"path":"crates/nyctos-types/src/project.rs","line":68,"cap":"MASS_ASSIGNMENT_HOIST_RECURRENCE","rationale":"Sixth, seventh, eighth, and ninth instances of the #78/#79/#80/#81/#92 meta-pattern in a single diff: CreateProjectRequest (project.rs:71), PatchProjectRequest (project.rs:91), CreateRepoRequest (repo.rs:104), PatchRepoRequest (repo.rs:124) all land in nyctos-types with #[derive(Deserialize, TS)] and zero per-field validators. (a) `name: String` on Create* has no charset/length cap, no DEFAULT_PROJECT_NAME deny, no Unicode-lookalike rejection. (b) `source_url_or_path: String` is plain text — feeds into git_ls_remote_probe OS_COMMAND sink without a scheme allowlist at the deserialize layer. (c) `target_base_url: Option<String>` on both Create+Patch feeds into the SSRF sink at compose.rs:231 (sentinel #2 / #88) without validation; pre-hoist the same gap existed in router-local DTOs but was scoped to one crate. Now any workspace crate that adds a Json<PatchProjectRequest>-shaped handler (replay-bundle ingester, bulk-import endpoint, MCP tool surface) silently inherits all four mass-assignment surfaces. (d) The unifying meta-finding from #81 mitigation (4) — workspace-level lint that fails the build on new #[derive(Deserialize)] in nyctos-types::* without an explicit `wire_input_audited` attribute — would have failed this diff at CI; the lint still isn't present. Recommended mitigations from prior findings still apply unchanged.","endpoint":"latent: any future Json<{Create,Patch}{Project,Repo}Request> route across the workspace","suggested_payload_hint":"verifier seed (nyctos-types/tests/wire_input.rs): assert_eq!(serde_json::from_str::<CreateProjectRequest>(r#\"{\"name\":\"\\u0000\\u0000\\u0000\",\"target_base_url\":\"file:///etc/passwd\"}\"#).is_ok(), true) — today passes (no validators); under wire_input_audited+validator mitigation, fails."}
