record_exploration_finding
{
  "path": "crates/nyctos-api/src/router.rs",
  "line": 772,
  "cap": "OWNERSHIP_ATTESTATION_BYPASS",
  "endpoint": "PATCH /api/v1/projects/:project_id/repos/:name",
  "rationale": "patch_project_repo (router.rs:735-792) accepts a new source_url_or_path verbatim (router.rs:775 patches the column with `req.source_url_or_path.as_deref()` and no validation of scheme, host, charset, length, or path-traversal grammar). The handler validates source_kind against the closed five-string set (router.rs:752-756) and re-validates auth_ref grammar (router.rs:768 via validate_git_auth_ref) but performs NO URL/path validation, NO call into git_ls_remote_probe (the OS_COMMAND-prone but at-least-test-gated path at router.rs:976), and CRUCIALLY no reset of i_own_this. The create handler at router.rs:681-685 refuses any POST without `i_own_this: true` (the comment treats this as operator attestation 'before the daemon will accept a repo'); the patch handler at router.rs:757-761 refuses to CLEAR the flag but accepts re-attestation as a no-op (`Some(true)` or `None` both leave it at true). Net effect: once a repo row carries `i_own_this: true`, an authed caller can issue a single PATCH that swaps source_url_or_path to an attacker-controlled URL (e.g. `ext::sh -c id>/tmp/pwn`, `/etc/passwd`, `http://169.254.169.254/...`) while the attestation flag silently rides forward as 'true', and the next scan/ingest run consumes the new URL with the daemon trusting that the operator vetted it. Sentinel #1759 names the OS_COMMAND sink on the test endpoint and on the create path (where i_own_this is FRESH); this finding names the SAME class of sink reached via the PATCH path where i_own_this is STALE and was attested against a DIFFERENT URL. The asymmetry is exactly the kind of state-machine flaw the exploration pass is meant to catch: each handler in isolation looks safe (create requires attestation, patch refuses to clear it), but the cross-handler invariant 'i_own_this attests THIS source_url_or_path' is never expressed in code. Compounds with: (i) sentinel #6 OS_COMMAND on ingest_git (the next scan after a URL-swap PATCH hits this sink with attacker-controlled URL + the unchanged auth_ref); (ii) sentinel #88 SSRF on target_base_url (URL-swap analog on the project row; this finding is the repo-row sibling); (iii) the four-DTO hoist findings (#95) — now that PatchRepoRequest lives in nyctos-types, any future MCP / CLI / replay-bundle handler that takes a Json<PatchRepoRequest> inherits the same ownership-attestation bypass. Static pass missed because the bug is the absence of a re-attestation hook on a sensitive-field write, which requires cross-handler reasoning over a state machine the codebase does not encode. Mitigations: (1) treat source_url_or_path as an attestation-bound field — any PATCH that mutates it (or mutates source_kind, since a kind change changes the URL grammar's meaning) MUST require `i_own_this: true` in the SAME request body and MUST refuse if any of {source_kind, source_url_or_path} changes value, forcing the operator to re-affirm; (2) emit an AgentEvent::AuditAttestation event (or extend the existing run-event stream) every time source_url_or_path or auth_ref is mutated, so operators see the rebind in the UI activity feed; (3) gate the rebind behind the `test` endpoint pipeline (run git_ls_remote_probe with the SAFE flags from the #1759 mitigation against the new URL before persisting); (4) at the type layer, add `#[serde(deny_unknown_fields)]` to PatchRepoRequest plus a #[serde(default = \"false_attestation\")] on a new required `re_attest: bool` field that the handler matches against `req.source_url_or_path.is_some()`.",
  "suggested_payload_hint": "Reproducer (against a daemon with a vetted git repo named 'app'): (1) `curl -X PATCH -H 'Authorization: Bearer <op>' http://127.0.0.1:8088/api/v1/projects/default-project/repos/app -d '{\"source_url_or_path\":\"ext::sh -c id>/tmp/pwn\"}'` — 200 OK; row now points at the ext-protocol payload while i_own_this stays true. (2) Trigger a scan: `curl -X POST -H 'Authorization: Bearer <op>' http://127.0.0.1:8088/api/v1/projects/default-project/scan` — next ingest_git fires the ext::sh payload and /tmp/pwn appears. Pivot variants: `\"source_url_or_path\":\"--upload-pack=/tmp/evil\"`; `\"source_url_or_path\":\"http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/\"` paired with `\"source_kind\":\"git\"` to make the metadata IP a git remote that ingest_git fetches. Verifier seed (router-level integration test in nyctos-api/tests/api.rs): `patch_repo_url_swap_preserves_i_own_this_today` — assert 200 on the PATCH and observe `store.repos().get('app').await?.i_own_this == true && source_url_or_path == 'ext::sh -c id>/tmp/pwn'`. Under mitigation (1) the same PATCH returns 400 with body referencing the re-attestation requirement; under mitigation (2) the integration test additionally asserts a new AgentEvent::AuditAttestation surfaces on the events WS within 200ms."
